{
    "info": {
        "_postman_id": "tent-backend-api-collection",
        "name": "TenT Backend APIs",
        "description": "Comprehensive API collection for `apps/backend`.\n\nFlow:\n1. Use **Auth > Signup** (optional) to create a user.\n2. Use **Auth > Login** to receive `auth_token` and `refresh_token` cookies.\n3. Call protected routes (`/auth/me`, `/user/*`, `/timesheet/*`) with Postman cookie jar enabled.\n\nTimesheets are derived from a flat `TimesheetEntry` model (no stored `Timesheet`/status):\n- **Timesheets > Weekly Timesheet Listing (API-1)** returns the derived weeks + computed status.\n- **Timesheets > Week Detail (API-2)** returns one week's day-by-day breakdown.\n- **Entries** create/edit/soft-delete individual entries (self-only).\n\nSeed users (from `@repo/db` seed): `dave@example.com` (MANAGER) and `eve@example.com` (EMPLOYEE), both `password123`. The seed gives `eve` one COMPLETED (40h) and one INCOMPLETE (17h) week.",
        "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
    },
    "variable": [
        {
            "key": "baseUrl",
            "value": "http://localhost:3000"
        },
        {
            "key": "userId",
            "value": ""
        },
        {
            "key": "weekStart",
            "value": ""
        },
        {
            "key": "projectId",
            "value": ""
        },
        {
            "key": "taskId",
            "value": ""
        },
        {
            "key": "entryId",
            "value": ""
        }
    ],
    "item": [
        {
            "name": "Health",
            "item": [
                {
                    "name": "Backend Root",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "header": [],
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": [""]
                        },
                        "description": "Sanity endpoint for backend reachability. Returns a simple JSON message."
                    },
                    "response": []
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Auth",
            "item": [
                {
                    "name": "Signup",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "POST",
                        "header": [
                            {
                                "key": "Content-Type",
                                "value": "application/json"
                            }
                        ],
                        "body": {
                            "mode": "raw",
                            "raw": "{\n    \"email\": \"new.user@example.com\",\n    \"username\": \"newuser\",\n    \"password\": \"password123\",\n    \"firstName\": \"New\",\n    \"lastName\": \"User\"\n}"
                        },
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/signup",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["auth", "signup"]
                        },
                        "description": "Creates a new user account. Enforces unique email and username. Returns the created user profile (without password)."
                    },
                    "response": []
                },
                {
                    "name": "Login",
                    "event": [
                        {
                            "listen": "test",
                            "script": {
                                "exec": [
                                    "pm.test('Login succeeded', function () {",
                                    "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                                    "});",
                                    "const body = pm.response.json();",
                                    "if (body && body.user && body.user.id) {",
                                    "    pm.collectionVariables.set('userId', body.user.id);",
                                    "}"
                                ],
                                "type": "text/javascript"
                            }
                        }
                    ],
                    "request": {
                        "method": "POST",
                        "header": [
                            {
                                "key": "Content-Type",
                                "value": "application/json"
                            }
                        ],
                        "body": {
                            "mode": "raw",
                            "raw": "{\n    \"username\": \"eve@example.com\",\n    \"password\": \"password123\"\n}"
                        },
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/login",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["auth", "login"]
                        },
                        "description": "Authenticates user by email/username + password. Sets `auth_token` and `refresh_token` HTTP-only cookies. Must run before protected routes. Seed user `eve@example.com` has timesheet data."
                    },
                    "response": []
                },
                {
                    "name": "Forgot Password",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "POST",
                        "header": [
                            {
                                "key": "Content-Type",
                                "value": "application/json"
                            }
                        ],
                        "body": {
                            "mode": "raw",
                            "raw": "{\n    \"email\": \"eve@example.com\"\n}"
                        },
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/forgot-password",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["auth", "forgot-password"]
                        },
                        "description": "Generates and stores a password reset token if the email exists. Response is intentionally generic to avoid account enumeration."
                    },
                    "response": []
                },
                {
                    "name": "Refresh",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "POST",
                        "header": [],
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["auth", "refresh"]
                        },
                        "description": "Uses `refresh_token` cookie to mint a fresh `auth_token` cookie. Fails if refresh token is expired, missing, or not the latest one stored for user."
                    },
                    "response": []
                },
                {
                    "name": "Me",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "header": [],
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/me",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["auth", "me"]
                        },
                        "description": "Returns current authenticated user profile resolved from `auth_token` via backend proxy."
                    },
                    "response": []
                },
                {
                    "name": "Logout",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "POST",
                        "header": [],
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/logout",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["auth", "logout"]
                        },
                        "description": "Clears auth cookies and invalidates stored refresh token for the authenticated user."
                    },
                    "response": []
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "User",
            "item": [
                {
                    "name": "List Users",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "header": [],
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/user",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["user"]
                        },
                        "description": "Returns all non-deleted users. Useful for admin/testing visibility."
                    },
                    "response": []
                },
                {
                    "name": "Get Current User Detail",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "header": [],
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/user/{{userId}}",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["user", "{{userId}}"]
                        },
                        "description": "Returns full user detail for authenticated user context. `userId` must match token identity."
                    },
                    "response": []
                },
                {
                    "name": "Update Current User Profile",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "PUT",
                        "header": [
                            {
                                "key": "Content-Type",
                                "value": "application/json"
                            }
                        ],
                        "body": {
                            "mode": "raw",
                            "raw": "{\n    \"firstName\": \"Eve\",\n    \"lastName\": \"Davis\",\n    \"username\": \"eve.d\",\n    \"profilePic\": \"https://example.com/avatar.png\"\n}"
                        },
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/user/{{userId}}",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["user", "{{userId}}"]
                        },
                        "description": "Updates the authenticated user's profile fields. Route enforces path user ID equals authenticated user ID."
                    },
                    "response": []
                },
                {
                    "name": "Update Password",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "PUT",
                        "header": [
                            {
                                "key": "Content-Type",
                                "value": "application/json"
                            }
                        ],
                        "body": {
                            "mode": "raw",
                            "raw": "{\n    \"oldPassword\": \"password123\",\n    \"password\": \"password1234\"\n}"
                        },
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/user/{{userId}}/password",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["user", "{{userId}}", "password"]
                        },
                        "description": "Changes current user's password after verifying `oldPassword`."
                    },
                    "response": []
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Timesheets",
            "item": [
                {
                    "name": "Weekly Timesheet Listing (API-1)",
                    "event": [
                        {
                            "listen": "test",
                            "script": {
                                "exec": [
                                    "pm.test('Listing succeeded', function () {",
                                    "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                                    "});",
                                    "const body = pm.response.json();",
                                    "if (body && Array.isArray(body.weeks) && body.weeks.length) {",
                                    "    // Prefer a week with logged hours so the detail call shows data.",
                                    "    const week = body.weeks.find(function (w) { return w.totalHours > 0; }) || body.weeks[0];",
                                    "    if (week && week.periodStart) {",
                                    "        pm.collectionVariables.set('weekStart', week.periodStart);",
                                    "    }",
                                    "}"
                                ],
                                "type": "text/javascript"
                            }
                        }
                    ],
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "header": [],
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/timesheet/weeks?page=1&pageSize=10",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["timesheet", "weeks"],
                            "query": [
                                {
                                    "key": "page",
                                    "value": "1"
                                },
                                {
                                    "key": "pageSize",
                                    "value": "10"
                                },
                                {
                                    "key": "userId",
                                    "value": "{{userId}}",
                                    "description": "Optional. MANAGER/ADMIN only — view another user's weeks.",
                                    "disabled": true
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        "description": "API-1 — Weekly Timesheet Listing.\n\nReturns the authenticated user's weeks derived from timesheet entries: a dense, gap-filled range from the first-entry week through the current week, newest first, paginated.\n\nEach row: `weekNumber`, `weekYear` (ISO 8601), `periodStart` (Monday), `periodEnd` (Friday), `totalHours` (sum over the full Mon-Sun ISO week), and computed `status` — `MISSING` (0h), `INCOMPLETE` (< weeklyCapacity), `COMPLETED` (>= weeklyCapacity).\n\nResponse: `{ weeks, page, pageSize, total }`.\n\nManagers/admins may pass `?userId=` (enable the disabled query param) to view another user's weeks; employees get 403 for others.\n\nThe test script stores a `periodStart` into the `weekStart` collection variable so the Week Detail request works immediately."
                    },
                    "response": []
                },
                {
                    "name": "Week Detail (API-2)",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "header": [],
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/timesheet/weeks/{{weekStart}}",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["timesheet", "weeks", "{{weekStart}}"],
                            "query": [
                                {
                                    "key": "userId",
                                    "value": "{{userId}}",
                                    "description": "Optional. MANAGER/ADMIN only — view another user's week.",
                                    "disabled": true
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        "description": "API-2 — Detailed Day-by-Day View for one week.\n\n`weekStart` must be a **Monday** in `YYYY-MM-DD` (e.g. a `periodStart` returned by API-1; the listing's test script auto-fills `weekStart`). A non-Monday or invalid date returns 400.\n\nReturns: `weekNumber`, `weekYear`, `periodStart` (Mon), `periodEnd` (Fri), `totalHours`, `capacity` (the user's `weeklyCapacity`), `utilization` (%), computed `status`, and `days[]` (Monday-Friday). Each day has `date`, `dayLabel`, `totalHours`, and `entries[]` (id, hours, workType, description, nested `project {id,name}` and `task {id,title}|null`).\n\nManagers/admins may pass `?userId=`."
                    },
                    "response": []
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Entries",
            "item": [
                {
                    "name": "Create Entry",
                    "event": [
                        {
                            "listen": "test",
                            "script": {
                                "exec": [
                                    "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                                    "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                                    "    if (body.entry && body.entry.id) {",
                                    "        pm.collectionVariables.set('entryId', body.entry.id);",
                                    "    }",
                                    "}"
                                ],
                                "type": "text/javascript"
                            }
                        }
                    ],
                    "request": {
                        "method": "POST",
                        "header": [
                            {
                                "key": "Content-Type",
                                "value": "application/json"
                            }
                        ],
                        "body": {
                            "mode": "raw",
                            "raw": "{\n    \"date\": \"2026-05-26\",\n    \"projectId\": \"{{projectId}}\",\n    \"workType\": \"Development\",\n    \"description\": \"Homepage Development\",\n    \"hours\": 8\n}"
                        },
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/timesheet/entries",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["timesheet", "entries"]
                        },
                        "description": "Creates a timesheet entry for the authenticated user (self-only).\n\nBody: `date` (`YYYY-MM-DD`), `projectId` (must exist & not be soft-deleted — set the `projectId` collection variable to a seeded project's id), `workType`, `description`, `hours` (> 0 and <= 24). Optional `taskId` — if provided it must belong to the same project (add `\"taskId\": \"{{taskId}}\"`).\n\nReturns 201 `{ entry }` (with nested `project`/`task`). The test script stores the new id into `entryId`."
                    },
                    "response": []
                },
                {
                    "name": "Update Entry",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "PATCH",
                        "header": [
                            {
                                "key": "Content-Type",
                                "value": "application/json"
                            }
                        ],
                        "body": {
                            "mode": "raw",
                            "raw": "{\n    \"hours\": 6,\n    \"workType\": \"Bug fixes\",\n    \"description\": \"Late ticket fix\"\n}"
                        },
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/timesheet/entries/{{entryId}}",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["timesheet", "entries", "{{entryId}}"]
                        },
                        "description": "Partially updates an owned entry (self-only; 404 if not owned). At least one field is required. Any of `date`, `projectId`, `workType`, `description`, `hours`, `taskId` (use `null` to clear the task). If `projectId` changes, the effective task must still belong to the new project. Returns 200 `{ entry }`."
                    },
                    "response": []
                },
                {
                    "name": "Delete Entry (soft)",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "DELETE",
                        "header": [],
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/timesheet/entries/{{entryId}}",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["timesheet", "entries", "{{entryId}}"]
                        },
                        "description": "Soft-deletes an owned entry (sets `deletedAt`; self-only; 404 if not owned or already deleted). Soft-deleted entries are excluded from all reads/aggregations. Returns 200 `{ success: true, id }`."
                    },
                    "response": []
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}
